Rating: 3
3 stars for ease of preparation and for being budget-friendly. Don't pay extra $ for the bottled marinated chokes. I used my mini-prep to chop a 12oz. can of artichokes and 2 shallots then transferred to a mixing bowl. Next added 1/2c. grated Romano and 2T. mayonnaise. I minced 5 large mint leaves and folded those in as well. Spooned the mixture into an oven-safe crock, topped with 1T. additional Romano, and baked at 350F for 10 minutes using convection until hot and bubbly and slightly browned on top. Served with crusty slices of baguette and a juicy, mouthwatering'07 Cakebread Cellars Sauvignon Blanc. Thorougly enjoyed by all.

