This is one of those recipes that stuns in its ease & simplicity. No it's not gourmet, but for 20 minutes of work it's really good & half of what you need is probably in your pantry. Consider going a little lighter on the cheese and onion in order to let the artichoke dominate. Add the mayo incrementally until you get a good texture: moist but not creamy. I stopped before half the mayo that the recipe calls for; any more would have been overpowering. A sprinkling of lemon juice was nice. Beyond that, you'll see in the comments that people have added all kinds of things... it's a great simple recipe that you can modify to make it your own.

