Rating: 4
A few of the first to review this recipe were disappointed because this was given such high ratings. Apparently they felt that if "lots of time" wasn't spent on a dish, then it just "couldn't be rated 4 forks"....well, I cook a lot....I love spending hours cooking exotic, beautifully prepared, gourmet meals. I don't mind spending hours in the kitchen because I honestly love it, but once in a while I run across a recipe that is so simple and quick to make yet absolutely fabulous in spite of the ease.....and this is that recipe! This is something I will make again and again. My family and I absolutely loved it! Two things I agree on.......use a good quality, fresh parmesan cheese and lightly toast the bread on both sides first. I also baked, rather than broiled mine so I didn't have to worry about the edges getting too brown. They are even better after sitting a while, at room temperature. Try these.......they are simple but fantastic! Nothing wrong with that combination!!!

